cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with task-oriented dialog systems and natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves training a dialog system to generate appropriate responses. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a framework for data augmentation to improve the performance of the dialog system. It may also be relevant to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it involves developing a software system for task-oriented dialog. Finally, it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training a neural network for dialog generation.
